# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# Problem: "nvm: command not found"
# Solution:
#   - Verify nvm is installed: which nvm
#   - Add to shell config: ~/.bashrc, ~/.zshrc
#   - Source config: source ~/.bashrc or source ~/.zshrc
#   - Restart terminal
#
# Problem: "Node version not installed"
# Solution:
#   - Install version: nvm install 20.11.0
#   - List versions: nvm list
#   - Check .nvmrc file
#
# Problem: "npm version mismatch"
# Solution:
#   - npm is bundled with Node.js
#   - Reinstall Node: nvm install 20.11.0
#   - Upgrade npm: npm install -g npm@latest
#
# Problem: "Global packages not working"
# Solution:
#   - Use nvm's local npm-g directory
#   - Or reinstall global packages
#   - Add to PATH: ~/.nvm/versions/node/*/bin
#
# Problem: "Different versions between developers"
# Solution:
#   - Ensure .nvmrc is committed
#   - Run: nvm use
#   - Verify: node --version
